[{"id": "6ca3070a-a709-4a30-b14f-66c7afff6deb", "chunk_index": 0, "text": "USER: Hi. i was just given early beta access to lagoon. where should I start?\nASSISTANT: Hey! Welcome in.\n\nFirst question: are you planning to run local models (Ollama) or use cloud APIs (Venice/Together)?\n\nThat'll determine your setup path. The short version:\n\n- **If you've got Ollama running already** \u2014 just fire up Lagoon and it'll find your models automatically. No API keys needed.\n- **If you want Venice or Together** \u2014 you'll need to grab an API key from whichever one and plug it in under Settings.\n\nFor the actual install: Windows users grab the .exe from the GitHub releases page. Mac/Linux, clone the repo and run `python setup.py` then `python app.py`. Browser opens to `localhost:5007`.\n\nDocs are here if you want the full walkthrough: https://genxillion.github.io/Lagoon/\n\nWhat's your setup looking like? And more importantly \u2014 are you here for solo writing, character chat, or something else entirely?", "embedding": [-0.011130116879940033, -0.09292326867580414, 0.02633003331720829, -0.0010666430462151766, -0.03763933107256889, -0.060828257352113724, -0.07841237634420395, 0.015917671844363213, -0.0349566750228405, -0.06383626908063889, 0.015370863489806652, -0.09863796830177307, -0.005174923222512007, 0.04633718729019165, 0.06449980288743973, 0.023703865706920624, 0.08465176075696945, -0.04813334345817566, 0.018468262627720833, 0.0320400632917881, -0.01188212912529707, 0.03396238386631012, 0.0011086190352216363, -0.0034159671049565077, 0.0005679271416738629, -0.0603778138756752, 0.0008156148251146078, 0.03914431855082512, -0.06092394143342972, 0.004320480395108461, -0.05928198993206024, -0.003504802705720067, 0.007287646643817425, -0.030305348336696625, 0.14144057035446167, 0.0005986036267131567, 0.041483163833618164, -0.10366052389144897, -0.1185164824128151, -0.06600227952003479, 0.019745662808418274, -0.017574366182088852, -0.043520621955394745, -0.014148794